“Name your price - I’ll meet you anywhere and any time.” This was the message allegedly sent to a DA councillor by a member of the Patriotic Alliance, who tried desperately to turn  him before  the crucial Nelson Mandela Bay mayoral vote on Thursday. But the attempt was in vain, with Nqaba Bhanga  re-elected mayor at the special council meeting, which had to take place as per a ruling of the Port Elizabeth high court. Desperate attempts to get some DA councillors to spoil their ballots were  part of the wheeling and dealing that took place behind the scenes before  the meeting, which dragged on for almost seven hours. For more on this article, please visit HeraldLIVE. 